file: sandbox/README.md
behavior: Documents that the sandbox/cage prototype has been retired and superseded by the `crates/ctx-cage` Rust crate, and records where each piece of the old Bash prototype now lives in the new implementation.
edit_notes:
  - This directory holds only historical Bash scripts (agent-demo.sh, cage-run.sh, broker.sh, broker-handler.sh, tool-client.sh, pty-relay.py, cage-demo.sh, stub-agent.sh, cage-adversary.sh, claude-preflight.sh, stub-claude.sh); do not treat them as live code.
  - Real implementation and behavior now lives in crates/ctx-cage/{src,tests,assets}; update this file's mapping list if files move there.
  - `--interactive` currently inherits the parent tty and drops `--new-session` instead of using dedicated PTY isolation; a portable-pty hardening pass is tracked in STATUS, not here.
functions:
invariants:
  - Target project root has no default; crates are auto-discovered under `<target>/crates/*/{src,tests}`.
  - Billed operations (task or interactive) require CTX_CAGE_ALLOW_SPEND=1; --self-test stub performs no spend.
external_deps: